{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 18:29:09.892183", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- No anomalies detected in control plane or data plane.\\n- End-to-end connectivity between hosts is healthy with 0% packet loss and low, stable RTT.\\n- All EBGP sessions across leaf, spine, and super-spine layers are Established, and routing tables contain the expected /24 leaf-host networks with appropriate next-hops.\\n- ECMP is active at the spine layer toward super-spines; leaves are selecting a single best path per prefix (expected unless multipath is explicitly configured).\\n\\nData-Plane Verification\\n- Host-to-host reachability:\\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 4/4 replies, 0% loss, avg RTT ~2.11 ms, reply TTL=61 (consistent with a 3-hop Clos path leaf–spine–leaf).\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: 4/4 replies, 0% loss, avg RTT ~2.49 ms, TTL=61.\\n- Wider sampling (lab matrix) shows 0% loss across tested pairs and RTTs in the 1–5 ms range, indicating no congestion or packet drops.\\n\\nControl-Plane Verification (FRR/BGP)\\n- Leaf routers:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 EBGP neighbors Established (AS 65100–65103). Receives expected prefixes. Routing table:\\n    - Connected: 10.0.0.0/24 (host subnet)\\n    - BGP-learned: 10.0.1.0/24–10.0.3.0/24 via a spine (172.16.0.40); 10.1.x/24 via another spine (172.16.0.32)\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 EBGP neighbors Established (AS 65100–65103). Routing table mirrors the above with its local 10.0.1.0/24 connected and others via spines.\\n- Spine routers:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 6 EBGP neighbors Established (2 super-spines in AS 65000, and multiple leaves in different ASes). Routing table shows:\\n    - 10.0.x/24 via leaf next-hops (e.g., 172.16.0.33/0.35/0.37/0.39)\\n    - 10.1.x/24 via both super-spine links with ECMP (two next-hops installed)\\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): Same state/pattern as spine_router_0_0; ECMP toward super-spines present.\\n- Super-spine:\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 8 EBGP neighbors Established (multiple spines). Routing table contains:\\n    - 10.0.x/24 learned via spines (e.g., next-hop 172.16.0.3)\\n    - 10.1.x/24 via other spines (e.g., next-hop 172.16.0.9)\\n- All Up/Down timers ~00:00:50–00:00:56 across sessions indicate a recent startup but stable peering with non-zero PfxRcd values:\\n  - Leaves: State/PfxRcd = 7 from each spine neighbor (consistent with distribution of multiple /24s)\\n  - Spines: State/PfxRcd values align with receiving host /24s from leaves and aggregate learned routes from super-spines\\n  - Super-spine: Established with all spines, receiving expected /24s\\n\\nRouting Table Observations\\n- Leaves have a single best path per destination prefix (no multipath), splitting destinations across different spines based on BGP best-path selection. This is not inherently abnormal for EBGP without multipath configured.\\n- Spines show ECMP toward super-spines for remote pod subnets, which is consistent with Clos design.\\n\\nFindings and Assessment\\n- No reachability issues between the provided hosts (pc_0_0 and pc_0_1); RTT and TTL values are consistent with the expected Clos path length.\\n- No packet loss observed in targeted and broad reachability tests.\\n- All BGP sessions are Established across tiers with reasonable prefix counts; no stuck adjacencies or flapping observed.\\n- The routing fabric is distributing routes correctly; next-hops are appropriate for the topology.\\n- ECMP is functioning at the spine layer. Leaves select single best paths per prefix; this is acceptable unless equal-cost multipath is a specific design requirement at the leaf layer.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Network health is normal. No faulty devices or misconfigurations identified based on the current state.\\n- Control-plane and data-plane behaviors align with the expected multi-tier EBGP Clos topology., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='745b50f1-72c1-4e8f-a694-d6c02ba4fa7a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
